the discovery of the Nazca Lines. The Nazca Lines are a series of geoglyphs located in the Nazca Desert in southern Peru. The lines were created by removing the reddish-brown iron oxide coating from the surface of the ground. The lines are so large that they can only be seen from the air. The lines are thought to have been created by the Nazca culture between 500 BCE and 500 CE. The Nazca Lines are one of the most important archaeological sites in the world.
